aw Jesus Story\n|\nNothingwould beeasier withoutyou,because youare everything,all of it-sprinkles, quarks, giantdonuts, eggs sunny-side up-youare the ever-expandinguniverseto me.\n\n- Kate DiCamillo, Flora and Ulysses: The Illuminated Adventures\n|\nThere are few reasons for telling the truth, but for lying the number is infinite.\n\n- Carlos Ruiz Zafón, The Shadow of the Wind\n|\nLoyalty to others speaks volumes about loyalty to self. To love others, one must truly love him/herself first.\n\n- Peprah\n|\nWhat he knew, he knew from books, and books lied, they made things prettier.\n\n- Hanya Yanagihara, A Little Life\n|\nDon't just write a 'To Do' list. Write a 'To Be' list.\n\n- Karen\n|\nCommon sense comes not just from knowledge, but also from wisdom.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nWithout causality in the world, there is no point in educating people, or making any moral or political appeal.\n\n- Felix Alba-Juez, The Perception of Time... and its Measurement\n|\nConsult.../what reinforcement we may gain from hope,/If not, what resolution from despair.\n\n- John Milton, Paradise Lost\n|\nHappy people can look back and say they chose their life, not settled for it.\n\n- Shannon\n|\nLimitation is just an 'imitation' of the limit. Nothing real, just mindset.\n\n- Alin\n|\nOur love for our country is worth nothing if it deprives us of our sense of humanity, if it destroys positive consensus.\n\n- Janvier\n|\nI wear my past around my shoulders as a fine, but worn, cloak. Don't be fooled by my cloak's appearance, I have a three piece underneath.\n\n- Hubert\n|\nHey, I write fiction. I just make this stuff up, unless I get my hands on some good juicy truth. You know the kind I'm talking about ... that stranger-than variety.\n\n- Dick\n|\nOur battered suitcases were piled on the sidewalk again; we had longer ways to go. But no matter, the road is life\n\n- Jack Kerouac, On the Road\n|\nBut now, you are twain, you are cloven apartFlesh of his flesh, but heart of my heart.\n\n- Algernon