ssed by the desire to be useful for God on this earth, He will honor you, you will prosper and your life will be a testimony of success\n\n- Sunday\n|\nWhen the going gets tough, people bail. When the going gets easy, people get lazy. Honest, smart, hard work is the way to get results.\n\n- Richie\n|\nTo become better you, look nowhere else for greatness. All you need to improve and succeed are right there in you.\n\n- Israelmore Ayivor, Become a Better You\n|\nInspiration may be a form of super-consciousness, orperhaps of subconsciousness—I wouldn't know. But I amsure it is the antithesis of self-consciousness.\n\n- Aaron\n|\nHe lifted himself out of the darkness of his fears, into a bright new world of possibility.\n\n- Scott\n|\nWhen the time is ripe for certain things, these things appear in different places in the manner of violets coming to light in early spring.\n\n- Farkas\n|\nA virtuos woman is not moved by big names and flamboyance, but only men of profound wisdom and integrity move her.\n\n- Michael\n|\nKnowledge has a great power. Therefore, unethical use of knowledge can be extremely harmful.\n\n- Eraldo\n|\nIf you can tell stories, create characters, devise incidents, and have sincerity and passion, it doesn't matter a damn how you write.\n\n- W.\n|\nFor the human experience, life in the natural world seems to require the application of meaning, in order to evoke purpose.\n\n- T.F. Hodge, From Within I Rise: Spiritual Triumph Over Death and Conscious Encounters with 'The Divine Presence'\n|\nOf course, in fairness, I must remind you of this: that we writers are the most lily-livered of all craftsmen. We expect more, for the most peewee efforts, than any other people.\n\n- Brenda Ueland, If You Want to Write: A Book about Art, Independence and Spirit\n|\nThe danger is that in reaction to abuses and distortions of an idea, we'll reject it completely. And in the process miss out on the good of it, the worth of it, the truth of it.\n\n- Rob Bell, Sex God: 